          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "CYCLO"
                ],
                "institute": "1USAUSA"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Crocker Laboratory, 60-inch cyclotron"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Holmium oxide, containing",
                "about 15% dysprosium oxide and",
                "about 5% yttrium oxide."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV",
                "CHSEP"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "",
                "Bombardments with 38, 30 and 20 MeV alpha-particles.",
                "Beam intensities were taken from the cyclotron",
                "instruments.",
                "Initially the impure oxides were bombarded and the rare",
                "earths separated by the column method; in subsequent",
                "bombardments the recovered pure rare earths were used."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "GEMUC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " End-on type Geiger-Muller counters",
                "with 3 mg/cm2 mica windows,",
                "filled with 10 cm argon and 0.5 cm alcohol.",
                "A magnetic counter was also used which enabled",
                "recognition of positive and negative electrons and",
                "provided a check on data obtained from absorption",
                "measurements.",
                "In gamma-ray absorptions, lead screens up to 45 g/cm2",
                "were used with a beryllium absorber, sufficient to",
                "remove all secondary electrons, placed directly below",
                "the counter window. Measurements were taken on a",
                "counter tube without the usual lead housing, as",
                "scattering in the latter has been found to give high",
                "values for the absorption half-thickness of hard",
                "gamma-radiation.",
                "The counter geometries were calibrated by use of a",
                "weighed uranium (UX2) standard."
              ]
            }
          ],
